The paper discusses the use of technology for mental well-being, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) aspects. The paper also discusses the use of sensing devices (cs.CE) and feedback interfaces (cs.SI) for mental health monitoring. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning algorithms (cs.CL) for data analysis.
